I driven across and through streams, up and down mountains, dirt, gravel, etc.

You can roll one over. They are narrow and tall. I've gotten mine stuck on 
wet grass though.

Take straps, chains, and winches wherever you go.

It can handle it but you'll be replacing suspension parts (bushings, etc) 
every 300K versus every 500K miles!! <grin>


